headline: 3 Reasons to Sell WBA and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: In a sliding market, Walgreens has defied the odds, trading up to $11.26 per share. Its 25.4% gain since December 2024 has outpaced the S&P 500’s 2.4% drop. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
